Package edu.ncsu.csc216.collections.list

Class SortedListTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.collections.list.SortedListTest
  • public class SortedListTest
extends java.lang.Object
    Test class for sorted list. Tests various method calls of sorted list to ensure all methods are functioning properly as as described by the SortedList API
    Author:
    Christopher Wagner

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      void testAdd()
      Test adding elements to the front, middle and back of the list, adding a null element, and adding a duplicate element.
      void testClear()
      test the clear() method to ensure it removes all elements in the list.
      void testContains()
      Test contains() method to determine if a list contains items that are in the list returning true, or false if the item is not in the list.
      void testEquals()
      Test if two list are equivalent or different.
      void testGet()
      Tests getting an element from an empty list, getting an element as an index less than 0, and getting an element at an index equal to the size of the list.
      void testHashCode()
      Test if the HashCode of two similar test are equal and two different test are not equal.
      void testIndexOf()
      Test the index of an item in an empty list, and index of various elements that are in the list and not in the list.
      void testIsEmpty()
      Test isEmpty to ensure an empty list returns true and false if the list contains elements
      void testRemove()
      Tests removing an element from an empty list, removing an element at an index less than 0, removing an element from the middle of the list, removing the last element, and removing an element at an index equal to the size of the list.
      void testSortedList()
      Tests that a list is generated by adding elements to the list
